---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import Schema from '../../components/Schema.astro';
import { SITE } from '../../lib/site';

const thermoPrices = [
  { item: 'Smart thermostat install (customer-supplied)', min: 169, max: 249 },
  { item: 'Smart thermostat + supply (Ecobee / Nest / Honeywell)', min: 329, max: 499 },
  { item: 'Add C-wire adapter (PEK or equivalent)', min: 75, max: 150 },
  { item: 'Whole-home zoned controller setup', min: 850, max: 1800 },
];

const faqs = [
  { q: 'How much does smart thermostat installation cost in Wesley Chapel?', a: 'Installation-only (customer-supplied thermostat) runs <strong>$169–$249 in 2026</strong>. Supply-and-install of an Ecobee, Nest, or Honeywell T9/T10 is $329–$499 depending on model. C-wire adapter, when needed, adds $75–$150.' },
  { q: 'What\'s the best smart thermostat for a Florida home?', a: 'Ecobee Premium and Honeywell T10 lead our recommendation list for multi-stage heat pumps (the most common Tampa setup). Google Nest Learning works beautifully for single-stage systems. Every model we install supports humidity control — critical in Tampa.' },
  { q: 'My system doesn\'t have a C-wire — can I still upgrade?', a: 'Almost always yes. We install a C-wire adapter (PEK or similar) at the air handler or run a new thermostat cable if the wall cavity allows. About 70% of Tampa homes we retrofit need some form of C-wire solution.' },
  { q: 'Can a smart thermostat actually save me money?', a: 'Ecobee and Google both publish independent third-party verified data showing 23% average cooling savings vs. manual thermostats. Real Tampa homes often see $15–$40/month summer savings once humidity-aware scheduling is dialed in.' },
  { q: 'Will it work with my heat pump and heat strips?', a: 'Yes — but it needs to be wired and configured correctly. A misconfigured smart thermostat will run your heat strips unnecessarily and spike winter bills. We configure the stages, lockouts, and dehumidifier control as part of the install.' },
  { q: 'Do you install commercial thermostats too?', a: 'Yes — Ecobee SmartBuildings, Honeywell commercial, and BACnet-capable systems for small commercial HVAC.' },
];

const related = [
  { href: '/services/hvac-installation-tampa/', label: 'New HVAC installation' },
  { href: '/services/ac-maintenance-tampa/', label: 'AC maintenance' },
  { href: '/services/heating-services-tampa/', label: 'Heating services' },
];

const areaLinks = [
  { href: '/service-areas/wesley-chapel-ac-repair/', label: 'Smart thermostat install in Wesley Chapel', note: 'Heat pump-specific configuration' },
  { href: '/service-areas/new-tampa-heating-and-cooling/', label: 'Smart thermostat install in New Tampa', note: 'Two-story zoning setups' },
  { href: '/service-areas/lutz-home-air-conditioning-service/', label: 'Smart thermostat install in Lutz', note: 'Older homes needing C-wire' },
];
---
<ServiceLayout
  slug="thermostat-installation-tampa"
  title="Smart Thermostat Installation in Wesley Chapel & Tampa FL | I Care Air Care"
  description="Wesley Chapel smart thermostat installation — Ecobee, Nest, Honeywell. C-wire solutions, heat-pump configuration, humidity control. Serving Wesley Chapel, New Tampa, Land O' Lakes. Call (813) 395-2324."
  h1="Smart Thermostat Installation in Wesley Chapel & Tampa, FL"
  eyebrow="Thermostat Installation · Wesley Chapel"
  subtitle={`A smart thermostat is only smart if it's wired and configured right for <span class="text-accent-400 font-semibold">your heat pump, your heat strips, and Wesley Chapel's humidity</span>. We handle the install and the commissioning — not just the wall mount.`}
  heroImage="/images/Presentation-t-14.webp"
  serviceName="Smart Thermostat Installation"
  faqs={faqs}
  related={related}
  areaLinks={areaLinks}
  priceRange="$169-$1800"
>
  <h2>Why DIY thermostat installs go wrong in Florida</h2>
  <p>Online tutorials make a smart thermostat install look like a 15-minute job. For a single-stage gas furnace in Illinois, maybe. For a typical Wesley Chapel or Tampa heat pump with electric-strip backup, humidity-critical setpoints, and often a missing C-wire? We see the aftermath every month: systems stuck in emergency heat, strips running in 75° weather, dehumidifier mode disabled, compressor short-cycling, and one memorable case where a homeowner shorted R to 24V common and fried the air handler's control board.</p>

  <p>The install itself isn't the hard part — it's the <strong>configuration</strong>. Setting the stage count, outdoor lockout temps for the heat strips, the dehumidify-to-humidistat control, fan circulation mode, and compressor-protection minimum run times. Done right, you'll see the savings. Done wrong, your bills go up.</p>

  <h2>Thermostats we install and support</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Ecobee Premium</strong> — best overall for multi-stage heat pumps. Built-in air-quality monitor and humidity sensing.</li>
    <li><strong>Google Nest Learning (4th gen)</strong> — best design and learning algorithm. Ideal for single-stage systems.</li>
    <li><strong>Honeywell T9 / T10</strong> — best multi-zone and wired-sensor support. Pro-grade reliability.</li>
    <li><strong>Mysa</strong> — for ductless mini-split and line-voltage heating applications.</li>
    <li><strong>Commercial</strong> — Honeywell commercial, Ecobee SmartBuildings, BACnet-capable controls for light-commercial HVAC.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The C-wire problem (and our solution)</h2>
  <p>Most modern smart thermostats need a constant 24V power supply — the <strong>C-wire</strong> (common). About 70% of Wesley Chapel and Tampa homes older than 15 years don't have one run to the thermostat location. When that's the case, we have three solid options:</p>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2 text-slate-700 mt-4">
    <li><strong>PEK or equivalent adapter</strong> at the air handler — the cleanest solution when the existing thermostat cable has an unused wire.</li>
    <li><strong>24V transformer + adapter</strong> for older 4-wire systems.</li>
    <li><strong>Fresh thermostat cable pull</strong> when the wall cavity is accessible — ideal if you're also updating.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Our smart thermostat install process</h2>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2 text-slate-700 mt-4">
    <li>Inspect the existing wiring, air handler, and equipment specs</li>
    <li>Recommend the right model for your system and household</li>
    <li>Safe power-down and removal of old thermostat</li>
    <li>C-wire installation if needed</li>
    <li>Mount and wire new thermostat</li>
    <li>Full configuration: stage count, strip lockouts, humidity setpoints, fan mode, equipment protection timers</li>
    <li>Wi-Fi connection and app pairing</li>
    <li>Test every mode — cooling, heating, emergency heat, dehumidify</li>
    <li>Walk-through with the homeowner and setup of first schedule</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Pair with an HVAC tune-up</h2>
  <p>A new thermostat is the perfect time to do a full <a href="/services/ac-maintenance-tampa/">AC tune-up</a>. We offer a bundle price when installing a thermostat at the same visit — you get the benefit of the new controls running on a fully dialed-in system.</p>

  <p>Ready for a real smart home upgrade? <a href="/contact/">Book your install</a> or call <a href="tel:+18133952324">(813) 395-2324</a>.</p>

  <h2>2026 thermostat installation pricing in Wesley Chapel</h2>
  <div class="not-prose my-6 overflow-hidden rounded-xl ring-1 ring-slate-200">
    <table class="w-full text-sm">
      <thead class="bg-surface text-navy-700">
        <tr><th class="text-left py-2 px-4 font-semibold">Service</th><th class="text-left py-2 px-4 font-semibold">2026 flat-rate</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="text-slate-700">
        {thermoPrices.map(p => (
          <tr class="border-t border-slate-100"><td class="py-2 px-4">{p.item}</td><td class="py-2 px-4 font-mono">${p.min.toLocaleString()}{p.max !== p.min ? `–$${p.max.toLocaleString()}` : ''}</td></tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <Schema
    slot="extraSchema"
    type="PriceSpecificationList"
    prices={thermoPrices}
    pageId={`${SITE.url}/services/thermostat-installation-tampa/`}
    data={{ name: '2026 smart thermostat installation pricing in Wesley Chapel' }}
  />
</ServiceLayout>
